HEADWORD: Chapfallen
<hw>Chap"fall`en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having the lower
chap or jaw drooping, -- an indication of humiliation and dejection;
crestfallen; discouraged. See <er>Chopfallen</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chapiter</ent>⟦br⟧
